<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Iranian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<H4>   Letter of Understanding Signed </H4>
<F P=102> LD0202145994 Tehran IRNA in English 1241 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, Feb. 2, IRNA -- Iran and Bulgaria inked a 
letter of understanding for expansion of mutual cooperation in 
various fields, at the end of a two-day official visit here of 
Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati. The memorandum of 
understanding envisage continous contacts between Iranian and 
Bulgarian political and parliamentary delegations and 
cooperation in the United Nations and other international 
organizations. 
  Activating bilateral economic, trade and financial 
relations, 
promoting cooperation in cultural and scientific areas and 
providing consular services for nationals of both countries are 
among other points included in the agreement. 
  Talking to reporters, Velayati termed his visit to Bulgaria 
as "constructive" and said his talks with the Bulgarian 
president, prime minister and foreign ministers were indicative 
of friendly relations between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

