<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NSD Not To Support No-Confidence Vote </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202164194 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the Council of Ministers on 2 February, a 
meeting took place between Prime Minister Lyuben Berov and the 
parliamentary faction of the New Alliance for Democracy [NSD]. 
The meeting took place at the invitation of Mr. Berov. 
  According to NSD Deputy Chairman Stefan Bozhilov, the draft 
budget, the proposed no-confidence vote, and certain general 
social and political issues were discussed at the meeting. The 
NSD adheres to its decision not to support the no-confidence 
vote proposed by the Union of Democratic Forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

