<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Workers-Peasants-Monarchists Party Formed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202192894 Sofia OTECHESTVEN VESTNIK in Bulgarian 28 Jan 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia OTECHESTVEN VESTNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [BTA report: "57 People Plan To Build Communism With the </F>
King"] 
  [Text] The Bulgarian Workers and Peasants Party [Bulgarska 
Rabotnichesko-Selska Partiya] [BRSP] was established in Stara 
Zagora. It intends to revive communism according to Marx, 
Engels, and Lenin but with the assistance of the king's "strong 
hand." 
  Tonyo Zhelev, the party's leader, declared himself in 
support 
of restoring the monarchy in Bulgaria. According to him, the 
key cabinet seats, such as the Ministries of Internal Affairs, 
Defense, and Finance, could be entrusted to the sons of Simeon 
Coburg-Gotha. The BRSP is trying to rally all unemployed and 
desperate people in the country and to struggle against greed 
for money and for equal rights and fraternity, he declared. The 
leader of the new party, which has 57 members from Stara Zagora 
and the neighboring villages, hopes that his party will be 
legally registered by May 1994. 

</TEXT>

