<H3> <TI>   PDSR, PUNR Sign Protocol on Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202130794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Esteemed listeners, during the broadcasting of this 
newscast we received a communique from the Romanian National 
Unity Party [PUNR], phoned in by PUNR Vice President Ioan Gavra, 
which reads as follows: 
  A protocol on a political understanding between the Social 
Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR] and the PUNR on setting up a 
coalition government was signed on 1 February in the evening. 
This openness achieved by the PUNR is the most important 
political moment in Romania life since the parliamentary 
elections of September 1992. Within the framework of this 
political partnership, the PDSR and the PUNR have established 
the scope of their cooperation at parliamentary, governmental, 
and territorial levels. 
  The assumption of the political responsibility of the 
government act by the PUNR will take concrete shape in the 
drafting of an anti- crisis and anti-inflationist governmental 
program capable of dynamizing the mechanisms of reform and 
privatization and of contributing to the efficient resolution of 
the people's social problems -- the communique received by 
telephone from Mr. Ioan Gavra points out. 
  Contacted also by telephone, PDSR Executive President Adrian 
Nastase confirmed the signing of the protocol and said that it 
is the outcome of negotiations conducted on the evening of 31 
January by the five parties of the parliamentary majority, 
namely the PDSR, PUNR, the Socialist Party of Labor, the Greater 
Romania Party, and the Agrarian Democratic Party of Romania. 

</TEXT>

