<F P=102>  AU0302121994 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0302121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federation of Free and Independent Trade Unions 
of Engine Drivers of Romania has sent us a communique that 
emphasizes that following a meeting of the Coordination Council 
of the National Trade Union Bloc [BNS] on 1 February, it has 
decided to suspend the one-day strike on 4 February as well as 
the general strike on 16 February 1994. 
  The Federation of Free and Independent Trade Unions of 
Engine 
Drivers of Romania, a member of the BNS, announces that it will 
abide by this decision and will not go on strike on those dates. 
During a meeting of the National Steering Council on 8 
February, the federation's strategy for the coming period will 
be voted on, the communique also points out. 

