<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus: No Damage, Danger </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302140294 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fire broke out today at the tap transformer of the 
third bloc of Dukovany [South Moravia] nuclear power station. 
Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus reported on this at noon: 
  [Begin Klaus recording] The fire broke out at 0712 hours and 
was localized withing 30 minutes. I stress that the fire broke 
out as a result of a fault on the tap transformer. This electric 
facility is located in an open area about 50 meters from the 
reactor hall. From this point of view, this fire did not at all 
touch the area of nuclear safety and, from the point of view of 
the internationally recognized scale that is used to assess 
accidents from the nuclear safety point of view, the situation 
was of the lowest degree of alert, that is zero. This means 
that there was no infringement upon nuclear safety or radiation 
protection, and no radioactive substances escaped into the 
environment as a result of this emergency situation. 
  There was even no need to apply any emergency measures to 
protect the reactor against the tap transformer fire. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

