<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR Reportedly Covered Muslim Moves </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20311A Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 12 Jan 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20311A </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "`Blue Helmets' Protect `Lilies'"] </F>
  [Text] Certain individuals without proper military uniforms 
are appearing on the roads in the area around Kalesije together 
with UNPROFOR personnel. The Serbian military consider this an 
unauthorized interpretation of the UN peace forces' mandate. 
  According to information obtained by TANJUG from 
highest-level military sources of the republic of Srpska, the 
Serbian side has gathered considerable evidence to conclude that 
these individuals are Muslim soldiers involved in reconnaissance 
of Serbian units' positions under the protection of UNPROFOR 
personnel. 
  "During the reconnaissance" the weapons of the "Blue 
Helmets" 
are turned toward the Serbian positions, though this is not 
supposed to happen. 
  The military of the republic of Srpska point out that 
UNPROFOR's mandate is not to establish peace, but only to 
provide security for the humanitarian aid convoys on land. This 
excludes any armed reconnaissance. 
  The Serbian side points at the fact that UNPROFOR has 
started 
building a watchtower north of Kalesija on Muslim-controlled 
territory, though they have no right to do so. 
  The Serbian military warns that the Serbian side will 
destroy 
the tower if the construction does not stop. Reacting to all 
the events taking place in the Kalesija region, the Serbian side 
has issued a strict warning demanding that the UNPROFOR command 
observe the mandate of the peace forces in the former Bosnia and 
Herzegovina to the letter. 

</TEXT>

