<H3> <TI>   `Muslim Terror' of Serb, Croat Civilians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302152194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1336 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Zvornik, Bratunac, 3 Feb (TANJUG) -- According 
to the latest reports, the level of Serb suffering in 
Muslim-held areas is growing and Croats are also being 
persecuted with increasing frequency, TANJUG has learned from 
sources close to the Srpska republic army. 
  According to the same source, many previous reports are now 
being confirmed by the Croat side in the former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The latest example is the HVO [Croatian 
Defense Council] report on Muslim terror against Serbs and 
Croats in Tarcin. According to the reports many Serbs and Croats 
have been imprisoned in Tarcin for a long time and all other 
Serbs and Croats from the area have been forced to join work 
details of the so-called Bosnia-Herzegovina army. They have 
been transferred to Zabrdje near Kiseljak where they have been 
forced to dig fortifications for the so-called 
Bosnia-Herzegovina army. According to Croatian sources Muslim 
forces in the area plan to use the imprisoned Serbs and Croats 
as a human shield in attempts to recapture certain positions 
seized by the HVO. 
  According to the latest refugee accounts the position of 
around 100 Serb families remaining in Zavidovici is extremely 
difficult, Srpska republic army sources said. [passage omitted] 
  Serbs remaining in Zavidovici area are threatened with death 
on a massive scale if international, particularly humanitarian, 
organizations do not intervene urgently on their behalf, sources 
close to the Srpska republic army warned. 

</TEXT>

