<F P=102>  AU0202163694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [The Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 2d Corps Press center report </F>
from Zivinice] 
  [Text] The heavy shelling, helicopter flights, and attacks 
on the defense lines are the basic features of the [Serb] 
aggressor's activities in the operational zone of the 6th 
Operative Group Zivinice. 
  Dozens of shells were again fired at Zivinice today. The 
prevailing view here is that the aggressor has decided to 
intensify combat operations so as to endanger the safe use of 
the nearby Dubrave Airport for humanitarian flights. It is well 
known that the United Nations are determined to open this 
airport soon, and it is also well known that the aggressor's 
side is rejecting this. 
  The general alarm in Zivinice has already been sounded three 
times today owing to the shelling. 

