<H3> <TI>   Solana Warns Valentic Over Troops in B-H </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302143694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Croatian Prime Minister Nikica Valentic today 
received Spanish Foreign Affairs Minister Javier Solana who said 
after the meeting that their talks related to the situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Minister Solana stated that if the reports on the 
involvement 
of forces from the Republic of Croatia in the war in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina proved true, the international community 
would have to examine that question with utmost seriousness. 
  Before returning to Madrid, the Spanish foreign minister 
will 
meet the UN secretary general's special envoy Yasushi Akashi. 

</TEXT>

