<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Tudjman's Popularity Rising </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202181094 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202181094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Zagreb GLOBUS in Serbo-Croatian on 28 
January on pages 2 and 9 carries an approximately 3,500-word 
report on the results of GLOBUS' "big" poll on the popularity of 
Croatian politicians and political parties. The report, 
entitled "Although More Than 90 Percent of Croats Are 
Dissatisfied, President Tudjman's Popularity Is Rising," does 
not contain any information on how the poll was conducted. The 
only information concerning the size of the sample is that 
"2,120 citizens were approached" and that "more than 1,100 did 
not refuse to answer the questions." 
  The results of the poll's question on the popularity of 
Croatian President Franjo Tudjman and Drazen Budisa, leader of 
the main opposition party, the Croatian Social Liberal Party 
(HSLS), are expressed in percentages and show the following: 


---------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
