<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Postponed for Consultations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202153294 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Zoran Vaskovic from the Serbian Assembly] </F>
  [Excerpt] The assembly session only resumed a few minutes 
ago, but, believe it or not, it is already finished. Actually, 
it has been postponed until Tuesday [8 February]. 
  The new Assembly Chairman Dragan Tomic stated that the 
reason 
for the delay in the session were consultations among the heads 
of the deputy caucuses. They were supposed to agree on the 
candidates for the [four] posts of deputy assembly chairmen. 
The meeting was not attended by any DEPOS representatives. In 
addition, only two people were proposed as deputy chairmen. 
Tomic thought that the best thing would be to hold more 
consultations and that the session should be postponed until 
Tuesday. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

