<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Offers Military Aid to Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202135694 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Zhirinovskiy Offers Military Aid"] </F>
  [Text] At the press conference in Podgorica, Montenegro, 
Russian ultra nationalist Vladimir Zhirinovskiy said if 
Macedonia asks for a Russian military aid, it will easily be 
given to it, "just like to any other Slavic country." MAKPRESS 
informs Zhirinovskiy, asked "why he never includes Macedonia in 
his list of Orthodox Christian countries," answered "we have no 
reason to argue with Orthodox Greece." 
  Referring to Zhirinovskiy's statements in general, Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev said Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is 
"not a political but a medical case." 

