<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Iranian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<H4>   Three-Year Trade Accord Signed </H4>
<F P=102> LD0202130994 Tehran IRNA in English 1145 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, Feb. 2, IRNA -- Iran's Foreign Minister 'Ali 
Akbar Velayati wound up a two-day visit to Bulgaria Wednesday. 
A three-year trade agreement was signed at the end of 
Velayati's visit. 
  According to the agreement, signed by Iran's Deputy Commerce 
Minister Hoseyn Noqrehkar Shirazi and Bulgarian Commerce 
Minister Valentin Karabashev, the two countries are to boost 
volume of bilateral trade. Furthermore the agreement calls for 
creating a balance in the Tehran-Sofia trade. It also calls for 
setting up of a trade commission to oversee implementation of 
the terms of the agreement, propose proper solutions for the 
problems and find ways of boosing bilateral trade. 
  During his two-day visit Velayati held talks with Bulgarian 
President Zhelyu Zhelev and Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

