<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Rejects Moldovan Referendum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202204994 Paris AFP in English 2040 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bucharest, Feb 2 (AFP) -- A referendum of voters 
in the former Soviet republic of Moldova on whether they want 
the country to merge with Romania has no more value than an 
opinion poll, the Romanian Foreign Ministry said Wednesday [2 
February]. 
  The Moldovan Supreme Soviet at the weekend approved a 
referendum question asking Moldovans if they wanted their 
country to be "an independent, integral state or to unite or 
reunite with another country," meaning Romania. 
  But Foreign Ministry spokesman Mircea Geoana said here that 
for the referendum to be valid, all Romanians should be 
consulted. [passage omitted] 
  At the other end of the spectrum, Russian nationalists in 
the 
self-proclaimed Dniester republic in eastern Moldova, who have 
been fighting to take their territory into Russia, have called 
for a boycott of the referendum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

