<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meciar Rejects Talks on Hungarian Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302125994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0900 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak prime minister [Vladimir Meciar] said 
that he is not willing to hold talks on the Hungarian minority's 
collective rights, because the rights of the Hungarian minority 
in Slovakia, as he said, are already excessive. 
  At a Bratislava rally of his party, the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia, Meciar said, we quote: There is complete 
freedom in Slovakia, therefore, those who want to leave can do 
so at any time. He added that the Slovak Government will not 
pursue a policy to suit certain circles of the Hungarian 
Republic. 

</TEXT>

