<H3> <TI>   Serreqi Cites Readiness To Join `Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202143594 Tirana ATA in English 1115 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 2 (ATA) -- The Albanian minister 
of foreign affairs, Alfred Serreqi met on February 1, in Tirana 
a high ranking NATO delegation headed by the assistant secretary 
general Mr. Moltke, who arrived in Albania on the same day. 
  Mr. Serreqi expressed the Albanian readiness to participate 
in the initiative Partnership for Peace and stressed that 
Albania will play an active role and will be a serious partner 
in it. Mr. Motke conveyed to Mr. Serreqi the greetings of the 
NATO secretary general, Mr. Manfred Woerner and concentrated on 
some aspects of the cooperation Partnership for Peace. 

