<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fire at Dukovany Nuclear Plant Extinguished </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302144594 Prague CTK in English 1429 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Feb 3 (CTK) -- A fault in the transformer on 
the third block of the nuclear plant in Dukovany, South Moravia, 
caused a fire at 0700 [0600 GMT], Petr Brandejs, a nuclear 
security official, told CTK today. 
  The fire which was extinguished at 0900 did not result in 
any 
leakage of radioactive substances and no one was injured, 
Brandejs reported. 
  The fault, which caused reactor output to sink to 30 
percent, 
did not affect the nuclear safety of the bloc, Brandejs said. 
The fault has been provisionally rated as zero on the INES 
scale. 

</TEXT>

