<F P=103> LD0102164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Feb. 1 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak on 
Monday explained to Finance Minister Marek Borowski the reasons 
behind the dismissal last Friday of Deputy Finance Minister 
Stefan Kawalec. The letter has probably reached the addressee 
by now, Ewa Wachowicz, the prime minister's press secretary, 
said on Tuesday. 
  Wachowicz did not disclose the contents of the letter and 
denied press reports to the effect that Finance Minister 
Borowski, unsatisfied with the explanation, has allegedly 
decided to quit. 
  Premier Pawlak dismissed Kawalec last Friday without prior 
consultations with Finance Minister Borowski. Deputy Prime 
Minister Borowski Friday asked the prime minister for a written 
explanation by Monday. 

</TEXT>

