<H3> <TI>   NATO Official Praises `Active' Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302130294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1043 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES 3/2/1994 -- A North-Atlantic 
delegation, headed by NATO undersecretary for political affairs, 
Gebhardt von Moltke, arrived in Bucharest on February 3 for 
consultations with the Romanian party on the next stages of the 
Partnership for Peace Romania has to traverse. 
  Gebhardt von Moltke told the press upon arrival at the 
Otopeni Airport that Romania was "very active" in the close work 
together with the NATO Cooperation Council. Heads of state and 
government of the NATO countries have decided to take an 
important step ahead in the military cooperation, he said, 
stressing that the Partnership for Peace "gives Romania the 
possibility to strengthen this cooperation." He said he came 
here to get more information and get this process started, being 
very interested in the talks that would follow. He added 
Romania was a partner of the North-Atlantic Alliance and the 
Partnership for Peace gave it the possibility to structure this 
cooperation to its benefit. 

