<H3> <TI>   Amendment on Penalties for Defaming Nation Passed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202183794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1536 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0202183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 2/2/1994 -- Romania's Senate 
passed on February 2 an amendment to the bill of changing and 
extending the Criminal Code and the Penal Procedure Code, 
according to which the amended criminal code stipulates that the 
public defamation by any means of the country or of the Romanian 
nation shall be punished with 1-5 years of jail. The amendment, 
passed with 75 votes for, 25 against and 5 abstentions, was 
promoted by Senator Valer Suian of the Romanian National Unity 
Party (PUNR). 

</TEXT>

