<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 1 (ATA) -- Well-informed sources 
in Tetove report that Mithat Emini, former secretary of the 
Democratic Prosperity Party of Macedonia [PDP], was arrested on 
January 28. The same sources relate this act of police with the 
arrest some time ago of nine Albanians, one of whom was in the 
post of the deputy defence minister. Despite statement by its 
number one, Lubomir Ferckovski, that the question is closed now, 
Macedonian police continued with other arrests. Detention of 
the former senior official of the main party of the Albanians in 
Macedonia is a warning that other arrests will be made. Another 
proof to this is also the fact that the date of the trial for 
the above group of Albanians arrested by the end of 1993 is not 
yet fixed. 

