<H3> <TI>   Human Rights Violations by Serbian Police Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302123194 Tirana ATA in English 1117 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [House-Searches and Maltreatments in the Ferizaj Commune -- </F>
ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, February 3 (ATA) -- The campaign of 
house-searches, maltreatment and questioning of parties's 
activists by the Serbian police continued also last week in the 
Ferizaj commune. Under the pretext of looking for arms, the 
Serbian police maltreated Shaip Avdullahu and his nephew, Aziz 
Arifi, from the Prelez village, though they had no arms. The 
Serbian police inspectors questioned the DLK [Democratic League 
of Kosova] activist, Mustafe Aliaj, asking him on how the DLK 
spends its money and if the DLK is buying arms. The DLK 
Information Commission in Mirash reported that Serbian police 
has recently searched 10 houses and confiscated the arms for 
which the owners had a permit. The Human Rights and Freedom 
Defence Commission in Ferizaj reported that a Serbian couple, 
Petar and Mira Gavriloviq, has broken into the house of Pajazit 
Gjoni although he has a contract for it since 1984. 

</TEXT>

