<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Announces 8 May Parliamentary Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402094694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0800 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here at home, the first round of the parliamentary 
elections will be held on Sunday, 8 May, Arpad Goncz, president 
of the Republic, announced in the parliament. 
  The president said he had made this decision so that a new 
and stable government could be formed as soon as possible. On 
the other hand, the elections should be as cheap as possible, 
with as many people attending as possible. He also said he had 
to take several other aspects into consideration; for example, 
that the day of elections should not clash with the graduation 
ceremonies in secondary schools and that it should not be a 
working day. In his speech, the president called the cleanness 
of the elections important because, as he said, the second 
ballot was perhaps even more important than the first one in a 
new democracy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

