<H3> <TI>   Seven Killed in Shelling of Sarajevo District </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402115294 </F>
<F P=103> AU0402115294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Network in Serbo-Croatian at 1100 GMT 4 February within its 
regular 17-minute newscast carries the following reports on the 
situation in Sarajevo. According to a communique from the 
Information Service of the 1st Corps of the Army of the Republic 
of Bosnia-Herzegovina read by an announcer, "a calm morning in 
the Sarajevo region was interrupted by enemy artillery shells 
that ended their lethal flight in the region of Dobrinja. The 
aggressor fired them from the region of Vranjes. They were 82-mm 
mortar bombs. There were three bombs and Sarajevo has thereby 
added one more massacre to its list. The victims of this one 
are innocent civilians." 
  Jasna Niksic then reports live from Dobrinja that "so far 
seven people have been killed and 17 injured, of whom four are 
extremely seriously wounded and have been taken to the City 
Hospital. This is the balance of the morning Chetnik shelling 
in the Sarajevo Dobrinja district. Namely, the morning was 
extremely calm, but this calm was interrupted by two Chetnik 
shells that suddenly fell on Dobrinja One as civilians gathered 
to divide humanitarian aid. This is all the information we have 
now. We shall report with more details in our next newscasts." 

</TEXT>

