<H3> <TI>   Government Memorandum on Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302141294 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A while ago we received from the Foreign Affairs 
Ministry a Slovak Government memorandum on our country joining 
the Partnership for Peace program. 
  The memorandum points out that the NATO summit brought 
closer 
the prospects of Slovakia's full incorporation into a developed 
Europe, including the economic, political, and security aspects 
thereof. The summit has offered further possibilities of 
involvement in setting up new models of cooperation within 
Europe by supporting the development of the European security 
and defense (?identity). 
  The Slovak Republic is aware that the development of 
security 
mechanisms is a process. These mechanisms will guarantee 
stability on the continent. This has been reflected in the 
proposals and programs put forward by the Brussels summit. The 
Slovak Republic will continue to pursue its initiatives aimed at 
obtaining full NATO membership, as well as the security 
guarantees that are needed for successful completion of the 
economic transformation and the strengthening of democracy, says 
the Slovak Government's memorandum about [Slovakia] joining the 
Partnership for Peace program. 

</TEXT>

