<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meciar Walks Out of Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402103694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0900 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0900 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The beginning of today's deliberations of the 26th 
session of the National Council scheduled for 0900 hours was 
postponed. First deputy chairman Peter Weiss told the deputies 
who were present that parliament chairman Ivan Gasparovic had 
left the parliament building together with Prime Minister 
Vladimir Meciar immediately after the unsuccessful talks held by 
the representatives of parliamentary parties this morning. 
  According to TA SR [Slovak news agency], this meeting had in 
effect ended after the prime minister refused to join the talks 
because Milan Knazko, chairman of the Alliance of Democrats, was 
present at the meeting. Vladimir Meciar does not recognize 
Milan Knazko as an elected parliamentary representative. 
Because the representatives of parliamentary parties refused to 
accept Meciar's request that Milan Knazko should leave the 
meeting, Vladimir Meciar said, according to parliament deputy 
chairman Ludovit Cernak, that the meeting was not legitimate and 
was anticonstitutional. Immediately after that, Vladimir Meciar 
left the room. 

</TEXT>

