<H3> <TI>   Poll Author Apologizes for Error in Data </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0302130894 Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA in Polish 3 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS0302130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Apology by Renata Wrobel: "January Results of Public </F>
Opinion Research Institute for RZECZPOSPOLITA; Correction: 
Coalition Loses Support"] 
  [Text] In my discussion yesterday of the results of an 
opinion poll conducted at the request of our daily by the Sopot 
Public Opinion Research Institute [PBS], I made an error. I 
mixed the table of November survey results with the table of 
results from research conducted in January, as a result of which 
most of the conclusions I drew are wrong. In today's paper we 
will present the correct data. 
  I would like to apologize to the readers and PBS for 
misleading them. 

</TEXT>

