<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Official Criticizes U.S. Report on Human Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302192694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1700 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hungarian Justice and Life Party considers that 
in our country human rights are violated only in that the 
administration of justice is slow and those who have fired the 
volleys are not brought in front of the judges. Therefore, 
Istvan Csurka, cochairman, considers the regular annual report 
of the U.S. State Department, which refers to shortcomings in 
Hungarian press freedom and the enforcement of minority rights, 
one-sided and biased. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

