<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shelling of Sarajevo Market Kills Dozens </TI></H3>
<H4>   Serb Officer Demands Investigation </H4>
<F P=102> LD0502173394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1624 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 5 Feb (TANJUG) -- In response to the 
massacre in the center of Sarajevo, Major General Manojlo 
Milovanovic, chief of general staff of the republic of Srpska 
army, demanded that General Rose, UN Protection Forces 
[UNPROFOR] commander for the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, urgently 
form a mixed team of military experts to [passage indistinct due 
to technical failure] Gen. Milovanovic asked Gen. Rose to 
include representatives of UNPROFOR, the republic of Srspka 
army, and the so-called Bosnia-Herzegovina army on the 
commission of experts. The commission should investigate 
ballistic and other circumstances under which the massacre 
occurred to establish which side committed the crime. 
  Gen. Milovanovic requested of Gen. Rose that the 
commission's 
work be recorded on TV cameras and in photographs and documented 
with all other necessary facts and data and that the world 
public be informed about it. If the Serbian side's request is 
not accepted, the main headquarters of the republic of Srpska 
army will suspend all cooperation with UNPROFOR and humanitarian 
organizations until the case is completely clarified and the 
world public informed about it, the chief of general staff of 
the republic of Srpska army stressed in a letter to Gen. Rose. 
He asked Gen. Rose to answer his letter by 1800 hours today. 

</TEXT>

