<H3> <TI>   Shelling of Sarajevo Market Kills Dozens </TI></H3>
<H4>   General Cot Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD0602113894 Paris Radio France International in French 1100 
GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Remy Hourdan from Sarajevo--recorded] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Remy Hourdan] [passage omitted] Standing in 
front of a pool of blood this morning at the scene of the 
attack, General Jean Cot had tears in his eyes: 
  [Cot] You can say what you want, but technically speaking, 
it 
is very very difficult. I am not trying to escape from this 
tragedy, but I am telling you that it is technically difficult 
[to say where the shell came from]. The day before this attack 
the shell that landed on Dobrinja came from Serbian positions. 
Everyone knows that. It killed 10 people. It is a difference 
of degree, but we know that that shell was Serbian. 
  [Hourdan] And we do not know about this one? 
  [Cot] Technically no. I cannot tell you any more. 
  [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

