<H3> <TI>   Shelling of Sarajevo Market Kills Dozens </TI></H3>
<H4>   Izetbegovic, Jackovich Discuss Massacre </H4>
<F P=102> LD0602190294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, the president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina presidency, today received Victor Jackovich, 
the American ambassador to our country. They discussed the 
latest horrific massacre in Sarajevo and decided that it was 
necessary to establish all the relevant facts about the incident 
as soon as possible. The American ambassador gave assurances 
that his country and its allies would do everything to prevent 
such crimes from happening again, and would take the necessary 
steps in that respect. 

</TEXT>

