<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shelling of Sarajevo Market Kills Dozens </TI></H3>
<H4>   Serbs: Muslims Responsible </H4>
<F P=102> LD0602194394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1918 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0602194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Sarajevo, Feb 6 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Serb military 
sources on Sunday evening said there were indications that the 
Muslim side is responsible for the massacre which occured in 
Sarajevo on Saturday, when 68 people were killed and nearly 200 
wounded. There are indications that the projectile which hit 
the market in Sarajevo could have been fired from the positions 
of the Muslim Army's Second Motorized Brigade, two to three 
kilometers north-east of Sarajevo, Bosnian Serb military sources 
told TANJUG. 
  The Bosnian Serbs on Saturday categorically denied being 
responsible for the crime, and called for the immediate setting 
up of a joint commission of representatives of the U.N. 
Protection Force (UNPROFOR), the Serb and Muslim sides to 
investigate the crime. The proposal was turned down by the 
Muslim side. UNPROFOR military experts have analyzed the crater 
left by the shell but have not so far been able to determine for 
sure from which side the shell was fired. 
  U.N. military observers at the Bosnian Serb military command 
at Lukavica and Bosnian Serb military sources agree on one point 
-- that the number of casualties is too high to have been caused 
by a single 120mm mortar shell. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

