<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shelling of Sarajevo Market Kills Dozens </TI></H3>
<H4>   Krajisnik `Certain' Serbs Innocent </H4>
<F P=102> AU0602202594 Novi Sad TVNS Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0602202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Novi Sad TVNS Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" statement by Momcilo Krajisnik, chairman of the </F>
Serbian republic assembly, to Novi Sad Television Dnevnik on 6 
Feb; place not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] What is certain is that the Serbs are not the 
perpetrators [of the massacre in Sarajevo]. In addition to the 
routine investigation that we conducted immediately after 
learning what happened at the produce market in Sarajevo, we 
also carried out an additional investigation, and we can say 
with certainty that the Serbs did not do this and that the 
Serbian side did not gain any political advantage. 
  It is impossible to grasp that the Muslims would do 
something 
like this, and usually when we know that it was not us we are 
inclined to blame the other side. We have reached certain 
conclusions that a third side exists that is very interested in 
massacres such as this one happening, as certain political aims 
of foreign factors in former Bosnia-Herzegovina are thereby 
achieved. This said, we cannot today identify this side. There 
are many parties interested in preventing closer relations 
between the Serbs and the Muslims. They wanted to undermine 
these talks precisely at the moment when we were making positive 
progress on establishing trust between Serbs and Muslims, and 
when we were close to an agreement similar to the one signed 
with the Croats. We cannot now say that we cannot exclude the 
possibility of this being the Muslim side, but one thing is 
certain, and that is that the Serbs did not do this [sentence as 
heard]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

