<H3> <TI>   Death Toll in Dobrinja Shelling Rises to 8 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402133694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0402133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jasna Niksic] </F>
  [Text] According to the latest information from Dobrinja 
Hospital, this morning in Dobrinja, Chetnik shells killed eight 
people, including two children, and 26 people were seriously or 
lightly wounded. After they were administered first aid, six 
people were immediately transferred to the City Hospital, and 
others received medical treatment and were then hospitalized in 
Dobrinja Hospital. The first results of the expert military 
teams in Dobrinja say that three shells were fired. Two of them 
were certainly of 120-mm caliber and the third is assumed to be 
of 82 mm. As the first results of the investigation show, the 
bombs were fired from Lukavica, that is, the Chetnik lair of the 
Slobodan Princip-Seljo Barracks. I hope we shall be able to 
provide even more precise information in our next newscast. 

</TEXT>

