<H3> <TI>   Internal Affairs Minister Bans Public Gatherings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502191994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have just received a statement from the Internal 
Affairs Ministry Information Service. We carry the statement in 
full: 
  In accordance with the decision of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina of 5 February this year, Internal Affairs 
Minister Bakir Alispahic has issued an order banning all public 
gatherings from 0500 to 2200 on the territory of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. [Words indistinct] and other open air 
public places where humanitarian and other aid is distributed. 
  Exempt from this order are members of the Internal Affairs 
Ministry directly in charge of duties within the sphere of 
internal affairs [police], members of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army on military duty, firemen, and medical teams. Appropriate 
measures will be taken against all those who do not comply with 
this order. 

</TEXT>

