<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Akashi Says Mediation Effort `Failed' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0602194194 Paris AFP in English 1930 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0602194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, Feb 6 (AFP) -- UN special representative 
Yasushi Akashi said in Sarajevo Sunday [6 February] that his 
mediation effort in Sarajevo for a ceasefire had failed. He 
told reporters after meeting with both Bosnian and Serb 
officials: "I regret to tell you that these discussions have not 
reached an agreement yet." 
  "The major difference is that the Bosnian side wants to have 
the withdrawal of artillery, mortars and other heavy weapons out 
of range of the city of Sarajevo and be placed under UNPROFOR 
(UN Protection Force) control. This is not acceptable for the 
Serb side," Akashi said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

