<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HVO Continues `Merciless' Attacks on Mostar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702095794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0702095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Rasusic and Faruk Hajder from the </F>
Information Service of the 4th Army Corps] 
  [Text] Exploiting the attention of the international media 
and politicians on Sarajevo to the maximum, members of the HVO 
[Croatian Defense Council] and the Croatian Army continued their 
merciless artillery attacks on the lines of separation and 
civilian parts of the free parts of the Mostar commune. A 
sudden mortar attack on Blagaj from the positions of the Ustasha 
forces left one person dead. Several persons were wounded in 
this treacherous attack. The central part of the town and the 
defense lines in this part of the town were subjected to 
intensified attacks by the aggressor all day yesterday and 
throughout the night. 
  Over 80 tank and mortar shells were fired on the central 
part 
of the town from the enemy's positions on the left side [of the 
Neretva River]. These were accompanied by constant fire from 
infantry weapons. In addition to firing dozens of mortar 
projectiles on the Bijelo Polje region yesterday, the Ustashas 
attacked civilian targets in Potoci with multiple rocket 
launchers on three occasions yesterday, killing two civilians. 
  At 0815 this morning, Ustashas fired several projectiles 
from 
multiple rocket launcher on the city center, fortunately, 
without tragic consequences. Despite the stepped up attacks by 
the aggressor, the attained defense lines remain unchanged and 
are under the control of the 4th corps. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

