<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reportedly Repel Muslim Attack in Bihac </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602212394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2054 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Petrovac, Srbobran, 6 Feb (TANJUG) -- A 120mm 
mortar attack was launched on the Srbobran [Donji Vakuf] town 
center this afternoon from Muslim strongholds north of Bugojno. 
A general alert was sounded in the town and people were in 
their shelters and basements. [passage omitted] 
  Members of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 5th Corps today used 
all available weapons to fiercely target the republic of Srpska 
army position's along the Bihac front from their strongholds in 
the Una River valley, Serbian military sources said. According 
to [Serbian] military sources, two soldiers of the 2nd [Bosnian] 
Krajina Corps of the republic of Srpska army were killed and 
three civilians were lightly wounded in the attacks. The 
Serbian side was forced to respond and it repelled the Muslim 
attack successfully. Serbian soldiers have captured Barakovac, 
the most important strategic point on the Bihac front. 

</TEXT>

