<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio Says Mladic Preparing New Offensive </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702115094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0702115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Smajil Terzic from the Information Center of the </F>
Seven South Operations Group] 
  [Text] [words indistinct] aggressor is not keeping quiet. 
In the last 24 hours it attacked civilian targets in Sije, 
Kalosevic, and Potocic. It is amassing huge forces and hardware 
in the zone of operations of the independent battalion [word 
indistinct]. Intensive combat activities are an interlude into 
a new offensive that is being prepared by the criminal Mladic, 
using troops from Serbia and Russian and other mercenaries. 
Tanks and tank drivers are being brought from the so-called 
Yugoslav Army. It plans to extensively use aircraft, chemical 
agents, and surface-to-surface missiles, and carry out assaults, 
and subversive and terrorist actions. 
  It is known for sure that the aggressor has concentrated 
toward our units the forces of more than 20,000 troops, over 200 
tanks and heavy artillery pieces, and two surface-to-surface 
systems. Air support would be provided by aircraft from Banja 
Luka and Serbia. 

</TEXT>

