<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic, Tudjman Meeting in Rome Cancelled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702111994 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1019 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, Feb 7 (TANJUG) -- Croatian President Franjo 
Tudjman and Bosnian Moslem leader Alija Izetbegovic will not 
meet in Rome in the middle of the week as earlier announced. 
TANJUG has learned in Zagreb that the two sides have agreed 
that Bosnian Moslem Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic and Croatian 
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Mate Granic meet 
instead in Geneva on February 9. It is only if the 
Silajdzic-Granic talks produce some results that a decision on a 
Tudjman-Izetbegovic meeting will be taken. The venue and date 
of the meeting would be subsequently set. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

