<H3> <TI>   Shell With `Special Fuse' Used in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602222394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2100 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] A convention of military psychologists entitled 
The Treatment of Combat Stress Reactions, which will 
take place over the next two days chaired by Warren Dale, the 
director of the San Francisco trauma program, opened this 
evening at the Croatian military academy. [passage omitted] 
  In his speech, General Janko Bobetko, the chief of general 
staff of the Croatian Army, mentioned yesterday's massacre in 
Sarajevo. 
  [Begin Bobetko recording] The attack was very organized, 
with 
propaganda immediately saying that it was one shell and that it 
was by chance. This is not true. It was a shell with a special 
fuse, that under an angle of 60 degrees has an impact within a 
60-90 meter radius, causing 70-80 percent mortal injuries. It 
can be fired from a distance of three to four kilometers. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

