<H3> <TI>   Slovene Prime Minister Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702120594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the Slovene Government, headed by 
Slovene Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek, has arrived on a one-day 
official visit to the Republic of Croatia. The Slovene 
delegation was welcomed and greeted by Croatian Prime Minister 
Nikica Valentic in front of Banski Dvori [offices of Croatian 
Government in Zagreb] with all state honors. The two prime 
ministers and their delegations have begun talks behind closed 
doors in Banski Dvori. 
  Prime Ministers Drnovsek and Valentic are expected to sign 
several agreements: on employment, on cooperation in education 
and culture, on reciprocal implementation of court decisions in 
criminal law, on legal aid in civic and criminal issues, on sea 
fishing, and on economic and trade relations and cooperation 
between Croatia and Slovenia. 
  Slovene Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek and Foreign Minister 
Lojze Peterle are also expected to be received by Croatian 
President Franjo Tudjman. 

