<H3> <TI>   Satisfaction With Ukraine's Missile Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402142294 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1105 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our Ministry of Foreign Affairs [MSZ] has received 
with satisfaction the approval by the Ukrainian parliament of 
the Lisbon Protocol, which provides, among other things, for 
disarming nuclear missiles stationed in that country. Wladyslaw 
Klaczynski, head of the MSZ press office, told us about a 
statement on the matter. 
  [Begin Klaczynski recording] The ministry stresses that this 
is a significant step toward consolidation of world and European 
security. This step will undoubtedly open wider possibilities 
for comprehensive cooperation of the Ukraine with the entire 
Western world. 
  For us, for Poland, this is an indispensable factor for 
stabilization in the region. We would like to express hope, and 
the ministry expresses such hope, that the speedy implementation 
of the right and very important decision will take place. 

</TEXT>

