<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peterle `Still Waiting' for NATO Reply </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402162494 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1430 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0402162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today's session of the State Chamber Commission for 
International Relations was also attended by Foreign Minister 
Peterle. Regarding some criticism and various interpretations 
of Slovenia's participation in the Partnership for Peace plan, 
Peterle said that they were a result of lack of understanding of 
the matter. He emphasized that this plan envisages several 
groups of countries and corresponding procedures for their 
incorporation. A special procedure is envisaged for the former 
Warsaw Pact members, while a different procedure is envisaged 
for some other countries, among which is also Slovenia. 
Minister Peterle said that Slovenia is still waiting for the 
official reply of the NATO consultation council regarding the 
request to be included in the Partnership for Peace plan. The 
headquarters in Brussels have indicated that Slovenia's 
membership in the consultation council will only be possible 
when our country will sign the agreement on associate membership 
in the European Union, Lojze Peterle said. 

</TEXT>

