<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Owen Comments on Possibility oif Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702132494 Paris AFP in English 1252 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Feb 7 (AFP) -- European Community 
mediator Lord Owen was evasive Monday on the possibility of 
launching air strikes to retaliate against the weekend mortar 
attack in Sarajevo saying that only "a fool" would want such 
action. "Nobody but a fool wants air strikes but on the other 
hand nobody but a fool can go on tolerating the situation in 
which as many people can lose their lives as it happened 
Saturday in Sarajevo," Owen said following a meeting with 
Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic. The mortar attack 
Saturday occurred in a crowded Sarajevo market killing 68 people 
and injuring about 200. 
  Owen said his meeting with Milosevic centered on what could 
be done to avoid a similar tragedy in the future. He added that 
the meeting to be held Thursday in Geneva between Bosnia's three 
warring parties -- Moslems, Serbs and Croats -- "is not a 
meeting to discuss global peace settlement but to discuss 
confidence building measures." He said these measures would 
include setting up a "hot line" between the Serbs and Moslems 
that would lead to a demilitarization of the Sarajevo region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

