<H3> <TI>   Milosevic Condemns Sarajevo Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602152894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1500 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 6 Feb (TANJUG) -- I condemn the crimes in 
Sarajevo with the utmost bitterness, said Republic of Serbia 
President Slobodan Milosevic in a statement to TANJUG today. 
  "The dead and injured in Sarajevo are not the victims of war 
but the victims of war criminals. We all expect that these 
criminals to be found in the very near future and put on trial 
for the crime they have committed." 
  "The revulsion felt by the Yugoslav and international public 
is justified, and I sincerely hope that no political reasons 
will hamper the rapid discovery of the criminals and diminish 
their responsibility," said Slobodan Milosevic, president of the 
Republic of Serbia. 

