<H3> <TI>   Jeszenszky, NATO Official Discuss Membership Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402160794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1300 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Partnership for Peace offered by NATO is 
acceptable for Hungary only if it leads to full membership in 
the military organization. 
  Foreign Minister Geza Jeszenszky said this when he met with 
Gebhardt von Moltke, NATO assistant secretary general. There was 
a discussion on what Hungary could offer in exchange for the 
peace partnership. The work schedule mapping out the details 
for joint military exercises and training and peacekeeping 
actions were also discussed and coordinated. 

</TEXT>

