<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iliescu `Shocked' at Sarajevo Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0602144894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0602144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A statement by Romania's president, Ion Iliescu, in 
connection with yesterday's attack in Sarajevo has been faxed to 
our editorial office. Here is the entire text of this statement: 
  I was shocked and indignant at the news of this new 
irresponsible attack against the city of Sarajevo, which claimed 
a great number of victims among the civilian population who lack 
the protection of the city. We deplore the loss of human lives 
and want to express our profound condolences to the mourning 
families. We very firmly condemn this new barbarian act of 
terrorism and express the hope that those who have committed it 
will be identified and receive the punishment they deserve. The 
attack in Sarajevo does nothing but emphasize, in a dramatic 
way, the fact that resorting to force of arms prolongs human 
suffering, without solving problems, and it emphasizes the 
urgency for the necessity of a peace settlement in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina -- an objective to which all diplomatic 
efforts should now be devoted, the statement by Romania's 
president concludes. 

</TEXT>

