<H3> <TI>   Liberal Party Begins Extraordinary Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0502170094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0502170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The proceedings of the extraordinary congress of 
the National Liberal Party [PNL], which was convened by the 
initiative committee for organizing the congress, began at the 
National History Museum Hall this morning. 
  The congress is being attended by 475 delegates representing 
34 counties, all the organizations of the Bucharest Municipality 
and Ilfov agricultural sector, by representatives of certain 
political formations, cultural and socioeconomic figures not 
involved in political activity, and journalists. 
  The congress proceedings, presided over by Petre Dragomir, 
member of the initiative committee, began with the presentation 
of the political report, which specifies that the aim of this 
congress is to relaunch a political project of regenerating 
national liberalism and to elect a leadership made up of 
competent people characterized by genuine political legitimacy. 
  Greeting messages were presented at the congress by 
representatives of the Liberal Party '93, the Ecological 
Movement of Romania, the Romanian Humanist Party, and the 
Republican Party. 
  At this time, the congress proceedings continue with 
discussions on the political report. 

</TEXT>

