<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Campeanu Elected President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0502195494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0502195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The proceedings of the extraordinary congress of 
the National Liberal Party [PNL], convened in Bucharest by the 
initiative committee for the organization of the congress, 
continued this afternoon with the presentation of the report of 
the commission for the amendment of by-laws and voting on the 
proposals. The new bylaws adopted by the majority stipulate 
that the party be led by a president elected by the congress and 
a National Council consisting of 41 members, 21 of whom must be 
elected by the congress, and the remaining 20 to be appointed by 
the party president from among the chiefs of departments and 
counselors and submitted to the Permanent Delegation for 
endorsement. The representatives of county organizations and 
Bucharest Municipality proposed a single candidate for the 
position of president, namely Radu Campeanu, who was elected 
with a majority of votes. At this time, the congress 
proceedings are continuing with the presentation and submitting 
of candidates for positions within the party's component bodies, 
our reporter Iulia Gherman informed us. 

</TEXT>

