<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PNL Congress Concludes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0602202894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0602202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The proceedings of the extraordinary congress of 
the National Liberal Party [PNL] ended this morning. It had 
been convened by the initiative committee for the organization 
of the congress. During the two-day proceedings, the congress 
established the new by-laws, elected the new party president and 
leadership members, and discussed and endorsed the Program and 
Political Declaration of the National Liberal Party. The 
Political Declaration presented by Petre Dragomir declares, 
quote: We are now able to address the country and we want to 
participate, through our work and the values that liberalism 
promotes in society, in the development and modernization of our 
society, unquote. 
  At the end of the congress proceedings, Radu Campeanu, 
elected by the congress as president of the PNL, said that 
following this congress, the members of the leadership bodies 
who recognize Mircea Ionescu-Quintus as president of the party 
became mere party members. We do not exclude anyone, we do not 
wage war with anyone, but we believe that we have to conduct 
talks, to invite everyone to participate in a dialogue, Radu 
Campeanu concluded. We recall that at the Brasov meeting, the 
Central Standing Bureau of the PNL termed the congress in 
Bucharest, quote: A meeting of Mr. Campeanu's supporters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

