<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Businessmen Create Independent Confederation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0502183794 Tirana ATA in English 1138 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0502183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 4 (ATA) -- In a meeting held on 
February 3 by a group of representatives from the existing 
businessmen associations in Albania, the creation of the 
Albanian Businessmen Association, KOBIZ, was proclaimed. 
  The association will be independent from the state, 
political 
parties and religious communities. Its program stipulates that 
the confederation appears in the economic and social life of the 
country as an organization which will represent and support the 
interests of the industrialists, constructors, merchants, 
traders and all businessmen who will be organized in their 
federations. It will contribute to the strengthening of the 
democratic state and democracy in general as an worthy partner 
in the triangle state- trade-union-employer. 
  This confederation will be an active organization which will 
protect the financial position the Albanian businessmen in front 
of foreign capital competition. The confederation will have 
relations with its analoguous organizations in other countries. 

</TEXT>

