<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel on `Outrageous Scandal' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0602154894 Prague CTK in English 1532 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0602154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 6 (CTK) -- "The Sarajevo mortar 
massacre is an outrageous scandal. The action again confirms 
that every war leads to escalating cruelty," Czech President 
Vaclav Havel said today reacting to the shelling of a Sarajevo 
marketplace that left over 60 people dead. 
  Havel told journalists before his departure on a visit to 
India and Thailand that "in his view, the international 
community should entervene much more energetically in Bosnia so 
that this fratricidal conflict be stopped." 

</TEXT>

