<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Denounces Shelling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702152794 Prague CTK in English 1406 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 7 (CTK) -- Defense Minister Antonin 
Baudys said Saturday's [5 February] shelling of innocent 
civilians at Sarajevo market was the height of cynicism and 
monstrosity, ministerial spokesman Zdenek Borkovec told CTK 
today. 
  Borkovec conveyed Baudys's view on military intervention, 
lifting the embargo on arms exports to Bosnia and the possible 
breaking of Sarajevo blockade: These are seemingly simple 
questions but "in fact, these are the most complicated 
situations, one can meet in the world." 
  According to Baudys, the fighting parties should first of 
all 
bear in mind that the solution depends on their good will. 
External intervention is the last and most extreme solution, 
Borkovec quoted him as saying. 

</TEXT>

