<H3> <TI>   NATO Group Arrives To Discuss `Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402181694 Prague CTK in English 1546 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0402181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Feb 4 (CTK) -- To discuss the Czech 
Republic's relationship towards the North Atlantic Alliance in 
the framework of the U.S. Partnership for Peace project is the 
goal of a NATO delegation which arrived in Prague today, 
Director of the Foreign Ministry Press Department Marek Skolil 
told CTK today. 
  The delegation, led by NATO Deputy Secretary General Gerhart 
von Moltke, is scheduled to meet with Deputy Foreign Minister 
Alexandr Vondra and with members of the parliamentary Security 
and Defence Committee and Foreign Affairs Committee. It is also 
to meet with Defence Minister Antonin Baudys. 
  The NATO representatives came to Prague from Budapest where 
they discussed specific steps towards implementing the 
Partnership for Peace plan with high-ranking officials of the 
Foreign and Defence Ministries. On Wednesday [2 February] the 
delegation visited Albania, Bulgaria and Romania. 
  The delegation is one of the three NATO missions which are 
currently travelling the Central and Eastern European countries 
to discuss details concerning Partnership. 

