Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Feb 4 (CTK) -- Today's meeting between Czech 
Deputy Foreign Minister Alexandr Vondra and NATO's Gebhardt von 
Moltke discussed practical steps in the implementation of the 
Partnership for Peace [PFP] project. 
  Moltke, NATO assistant secretary general in charge of the 
division of political affairs, arrived in Prague today along 
with another four NATO officials at the end of a week-long 
Partnership mission which had taken him to Albania, Bulgaria, 
Hungary and Romania. 
  The Partnership for Peace project was adopted at NATO's 
Brussels summit in January. 
  The delegation provided the Czechs with further information 
on the project, Moltke told CTK, adding that he had supported 
Czech participation in the project throughout the negotiations. 
  NATO is ready for cooperation in military planning, training 
and exercises, including joint peace missions, he said. 

