<H3> <TI>   Visas Required for Travel to FRY </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702194494 Prague CTK in English 1807 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 7 (CTK) -- Czechs travelling to the 
Yugoslav Federal Republic (Serbia and Montenegro) will be 
required to have visas as of Tuesday, February 8, the Yugoslav 
Foreign Ministry has informed verbally the Czech diplomatic 
mission in Belgrade, CTK learnt today. 
  Zita Senkova from the Czech Foreign Ministry told CTK today 
that the information had not been officially conveyed to the 
Czech Republic. 
  The Czech Republic has been requiring visas from citizens of 
the Yugoslav Federal Republic, Bosnia-Herzegovina, Armenia, 
Azerbaijan, Georgia, and Tajikistan since January 15. 

</TEXT>

