<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jeszenszky Meets With NATO's Von Moltke </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402175494 Budapest MTI in English 1408 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0402175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 4 February (MTI) -- Hungarian Foreign 
Minister Geza Jeszenszky held talks with NATO Deputy 
Secretary-General Gebhardt von Moltke in Budapest today [4 
February]. 
  Von Moltke later told reporters he had come to Budapest to 
discuss implementation of the peace-partnership plan and help 
draw up a document in which Hungary would outline its 
cooperation concepts to Brussels. 
  His talks with Jeszenszky concerned the delegation of a 
Hungarian liaison officer to NATO's Brussels headquarters, and 
military-planning cooperation between NATO and Hungary. 
  Von Moltke described the peace-partnership plan as a process 
permitting cooperation on an extensive scale. He said 
preparations would soon begin for the first joint military 
exercise, to be held before the year is out. 

</TEXT>

