<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Pawlak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402202994 Warsaw PAP in English 1811 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Feb. 4 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak met 
at the Sejm on Friday with President of the Parliamentary 
Assembly of the Council of Europe Miguel Angel Martinez. The 
talk focused on issues that were already discussed in Brussels, 
namely, Poland's full participation in the European structures. 
  The meeting was attended by Spanish Ambassador to Poland M. 
Jose Antonio Lopez Zaton and Chairman of the Polish Delegation 
to the Council of Europe Tadeusz Iwinski, the government press 
office reported. Martinez said that negotiations aiming at 
peace in Bosnia and Herzegovina were now the most significant 
issue for the Council of Europe. In this context he spoke about 
the necessity to work out legal solutions concerning national 
minorities. Next, Martinez stressed that in his opinion 
mechanisms of authority in Poland have been stabilised and thus 
Poland was a reliable and valuable partner for the Council of 
Europe. 
  Waldemar Pawlak and Miguel Angel Martinez shared the view 
that participation in the Council of Europe was a chance of a 
better future for such countries as Poland and Spain, the 
communique issued by the government press office said. 

</TEXT>

