<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows HZDS Leading; Kovac Most Trusted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702112394 Prague CTK in English 1133 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, February 5 (CTK) -- Seventeen percent 
of Slovaks support Premier Vladimir Meciar's Movement For a 
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), while 14 percent support the 
Democratic Left Party (SDL) and just over 7 percent the 
Christian Democratic Movement (KDH), according to a poll by the 
Focus agency whose results were broadcast by Slovak radio today. 
  President Michal Kovac emerged as the most trustworthy 
politician (25 percent). Next came Vladimir Meciar with 21 
percent and third SDL Chairman Peter Weiss with 14 percent. 
  The poll was conducted between January 26 and February 1, 
and 
therefore its results were not influenced by the present 
political crisis in the Slovak parliament, the radio warned. 

</TEXT>

