<H3> <TI>   Supreme Court Suspends Privatization Dismissals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0802104794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0900 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0802104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the basis of its verdict pronounced on 8 
February, a five-member panel of the Supreme Court, chaired by 
Court Deputy Chairman Melkon Melkonyan, has suspended the 
resolution adopted by the Council of Ministers of the Republic 
of Bulgaria on 16 and 20 December 1993 on dismissing the 
following members of the Privatization Agency Supervisory Board: 
Nikola Katsarski, Yonko Kalpazanov, Dimitur Saraivanov, Todor 
Borilkov, and Lazar Buchvarov. 
  The Supreme Court established that the Council of Ministers 
has once more acted illegally by committing a breach of the 
Constitution and of legal acts. The Council of Ministers has 
abused its power, which is an inadmissible offense in a 
rule-of-law state, especially if committed by an organ that is 
responsible for the comprehensive administration of the country, 
the Supreme Court's announcement reads. 

</TEXT>

