<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Party Agrees To Talks With PDSR </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702163494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0702163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the proposal of the Social 
Democracy Party of Romania [PDSR] to conduct a dialogue with the 
opposition parties, the Executive Bureau of the Democratic Party 
[PD(FSN)] reiterates its readiness to participate in a dialogue 
-- a communique received from the PD(FSN) reads. In the first 
stage of the discussions, the PD(FSN) will be represented at the 
talks by the Internal Political Relations Department. 
  Another communique of the same political grouping refers to 
the statements made on 5 February by Mr. Mircea Snegur, 
president of the Republic of Moldova, and Mr. Dimitru Motpan, 
leader of the Agrarian Democratic Party [PDAM] of the Republic 
of Moldova. The PD(FSN) Executive Bureau considers that they 
are uncultured allegations with an electoral tinge, running 
counter to the historic truth and to the interests of the 
Romanians living between the Prut and Dniester Rivers. 
Regarding the proposal that the parties advocating the 
unification with Romania should be excluded from the political 
life, the PD(FSN) considers it as an antidemocratic gesture, at 
variance with the course toward democracy and pluralism assumed 
by the Chisinau authorities before their own people and the 
European democratic institutions. The PD(FSN), the communique 
points out, is deeply involved and committed to achieving closer 
ties between Romania and the Republic of Moldova. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

